-- Dollar Advances Versus Euro as Asian Stock Losses Spur Demand for Safety
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   R e y n o l d s
-- 2011-02-10T05:37:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/dollar-advances-versus-euro-as-asian-stock-losses-spur-demand-for-safety.html
The dollar strengthened against the
euro, snapping a three-day drop, as a decline in Asian stocks
boosted demand for safer assets  The greenback advanced to $1.3691 per euro as of 2:36 p.m.
in Tokyo from $1.3733 yesterday in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
